Primary Actions (Main Buttons)
Background: --primary (slate-900 in light mode, slate-50 in dark mode)
Text: --primary-foreground (slate-50 in light mode, slate-900 in dark mode)
Use for: Main call-to-action buttons, important actions, submit buttons
Secondary Actions (Secondary Buttons)
Background: --secondary (slate-100 in light mode, slate-800 in dark mode)
Text: --secondary-foreground (slate-900 in light mode, slate-50 in dark mode)
Use for: Alternative actions, less prominent buttons
Accent Elements
Background: --accent (slate-100 in light mode, slate-800 in dark mode)
Text: --accent-foreground (slate-900 in light mode, slate-50 in dark mode)
Use for: Highlights, special features, interactive elements
Destructive Actions (Delete/Danger)
Background: --destructive (red-500 in light mode, red-400 in dark mode)
Text: --destructive-foreground (slate-50 in both modes)
Use for: Delete buttons, dangerous actions, error states
Muted Elements
Background: --muted (slate-100 in light mode, slate-800 in dark mode)
Text: --muted-foreground (slate-500 in light mode, slate-400 in dark mode)
Use for: Disabled states, subtle information, less important text
Cards and Containers
Background: --card (slate-50 in light mode, slate-900 in dark mode)
Text: --card-foreground (slate-950 in light mode, slate-50 in dark mode)
Use for: Cards, modals, popovers, containers
Borders and Dividers
Color: --border (slate-200 in light mode, slate-800 in dark mode)
Use for: Borders, dividers, separators
Input Fields
Background: --background (slate-50 in light mode, slate-950 in dark mode)
Border: --input (slate-200 in light mode, slate-800 in dark mode)
Focus Ring: --ring (slate-400 in light mode, slate-700 in dark mode)
Use for: Text inputs, select boxes, checkboxes
General Text
Primary Text: --foreground (slate-950 in light mode, slate-50 in dark mode)
Secondary Text: --muted-foreground (slate-500 in light mode, slate-400 in dark mode)
Use for: Body text, headings, labels
Hover States
Primary Buttons: Use slate-800 in light mode, slate-100 in dark mode
Secondary Buttons: Use slate-200 in light mode, slate-700 in dark mode
Links: Use slate-700 in light mode, slate-300 in dark mode
Focus States
Always use --ring color with appropriate opacity
Example: rgb(var(--ring) / 0.5)
Disabled States
Use --muted for background
Use --muted-foreground for text
Reduce opacity to 0.5-0.7
This color system ensures:
Consistent visual hierarchy
Clear action importance
Good contrast for accessibility
Smooth dark/light mode transitions
Professional and modern appearance